reviews.review_text: Pick of the litter.... The best of the 4 uploads.   Great audience recording.  The Coliseum was small, impersonal, and very concrete.  This is a great effort.  Both are good sets for the time period.  The Kingdome, Tacoma Dome and Seattle Coliseum were just not great venues.  We probably would have gotten a couple more Dead shows in Seattle during the years if it was not for these audio challenged/clunker venues.

Love summer tours.... This show was alot of fun,6th show into west coast summer tour.  My oh my oh my the good old days.  I like the sound of this one better then other here.   That said this was not best of the tour yet it was alot of fun do to the deep elem and just the fun had.  Best were the boise and park west but looking back i see how lucky we were.  just look at what the scene had become at the end.   I feel i am lucky enough to have ben on tour during the paek years from 81 to 89.... not so much the latter.  although i did not miss a show from the late fall of 81 till fall of 89....    so many gems in those years
Really Good Audience Recording! Decent show, but get this for the colorful audience recording!!!!!!
